# Sword Health
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** digital health / musculoskeletal care
**Website:** [swordhealth.com](https://www.swordhealth.com)

## Overview
Sword Health is a digital physical therapy company that combines artificial intelligence, motion‑tracking sensors, and dedicated clinical coaches to deliver personalized, at‑home recovery for musculoskeletal conditions. Its platform replaces traditional one‑on‑one clinic visits with a data‑driven program that can monitor patient progress in real time, adjust exercises based on adherence and outcomes, and provide ongoing support through a mobile app and wearable devices.

The platform is designed to reduce healthcare costs, improve access to care, and shorten recovery times. Sword Health’s AI analyzes patient movement to flag errors and prevent injury, while the clinical team (physical therapists) remotely supervises and adapts treatment plans. By scaling physical therapy beyond the clinic, the company aims to address the high prevalence of back, joint, and muscle pain and reduce dependence on opioids and surgery.

## Utah connection
Sword Health is dual‑headquartered in Salt Lake City, Utah, and Porto, Portugal. Although the company was founded in Portugal, it established its U.S. headquarters in Utah in 2017, drawn by the state’s growing health‑tech ecosystem, supportive business climate, and access to talent. The Utah office houses leadership, sales, clinical operations, and product teams. Sword Health is frequently cited as a prominent example of the “Silicon Slopes” health‑tech boom and has received substantial venture funding from Utah‑based and national investors.

